{{italic title}}
'''''Earth System Dynamics''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[open access]] [[scientific journal]] published by [[Copernicus Publications]] on behalf of the [[European Geosciences Union]]. The journal publishes articles describing original research on the geology, climate change, and atmospheric science.<ref>{{cite web|title=Earth System Dynamics |url=http://www.earth-system-dynamics.net/about/aims_and_scope.html |publisher=Copernicus Publications |accessdate=21 August 2016}}</ref>

According to the 2016 ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2015 impact factor of 4.589.<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2016-08-22}}</ref> The [[editors-in-chief]] are Somnath Baidya Roy, Axel Kleidon, Anders Levermann, Valerio Lucarini, and Ning Zeng.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.earth-system-dynamics.net/editorial_board.html|title=Earth System Dynamics - Editorial Board|publisher=European Geosciences Union|accessdate=21 August 2016}}</ref> It uses [[open peer review]] system, where peer-review comments and replies are publicly available.

