{{distinguish|South Sea (disambiguation){{!}}South Sea}}
{{Infobox Lunar mare
|name        = Mare Australe
|image       = [[Image:Mare Australe.jpg|200px]]
|caption     = Mare Australe. The basalt-flooded crater [[Jenner (crater)|Jenner]] is near the middle of this photo, with [[Lamb (crater)|Lamb]] just to the right.
|eponym      = Southern Sea
|coordinates = {{coord|38.9|S|93.0|E|globe:moon_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}
|diameter    = {{convert|603|km|mi|abbr=on}}<ref name=USGS/>
}}

'''Mare Australe''' (the "'''Southern Sea'''") is a [[lunar mare]] located in the southeastern hemisphere of the [[Moon]]. It is 603 kilometers in diameter,<ref name=USGS>{{cite web |title=Moon Mare/Maria |publisher=USGS Astrogeology |work=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature |url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/SearchResults?target=MOON&featureType=Mare%2C%20maria |accessdate=2010-08-20}}</ref> overlapping the near and far sides of the Moon.  Smooth, dark [[volcano|volcanic]] [[basalt]] lines the bottom of the mare. The Australe basin was formed in the [[Pre-Nectarian]] [[epoch (geology)|epoch]], while the mare material inside formed in the [[Upper Imbrian]] epoch.

Unlike most of the lunar maria, Mare Australe has an uneven surface that is marked by a number of crater impacts. Examples of these include the craters [[Jenner (crater)|Jenner]] and [[Lamb (crater)|Lamb]], which are flooded with [[basalt]]ic [[lava]] much like many of the other crater features in this mare.

The [[selenographic coordinate]]s of this mare are 38.9° S, 93.0° E. The eastern half of the mare lies on the [[Far side (Moon)|far side]] of the [[Moon]], although it can be viewed in its entirety during periods of favorable [[libration]].
[[Image:Mare Australe AS15-M-2503 ASU.jpg|thumb|left|600px|Oblique view of northern Mare Australe on the moon, facing south, from [[Apollo 15]].  The crater [[Abel (crater)|Abel]] is at right, [[Gernsback (crater)|Gernsback]] is at left, with [[Donner (crater)|Donner]] in the left foreground.  The craters [[Lamb (crater)|Lamb]], [[Jenner (crater)|Jenner]], and [[Gum (crater)|Gum]] are visible on the horizon (from left to right).]]
[[File:Mare Australe AS14-73-10170.jpg|thumb|left|400px|A more distant view from [[Apollo 14]]]]
