{{For|the mountain range|Allahuekber Mountains}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Sarıkamış-Allahuekber Mountains National Park | alt_name = ''Sarıkamış-Allahuekber Dağları Milli Parkı'' | iucn_category = | photo = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | photo_width = | map = Turkey | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | relief = yes | label = Sarıkamış-Allahuekber Mountains NP | label_position = left | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Şenkaya]], [[Erzurum Province]]-[[Sarıkamış]], [[Kars Province]], Turkey | nearest_city = | coords = {{coord|40|18|07.27|N|42|36|52.04|E|region:TR|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | area = {{convert|22519|ha|abbr=on}} | designation = | authorized = | created = | established = {{start date|2004|10|19}} | designated = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = [[Ministry of Forest and Water Management (Turkey)|Ministry of Forest and Water Management]] | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = {{URL|http://www.milliparklar.gov.tr/mp/sarikamisallahuekberdaglari/index.htm}} | child = | embedded = }} '''Sarıkamış-Allahuekber Mountains National Park''' ({{lang-tr|Sarıkamış-Allahuekber Dağları Milli Parkı}})), established on October 19, 2004, is a [[national park]] in northeastern Turkey. The national park stretches over the mountain range of [[Allahuekber Mountains]] and is located on the province border of [[Erzurum Province|Erzurum]] and [[Kars Province|Kars]].<ref name="mp"/>
It covers an area of {{convert|22519|ha|abbr=on}} at an average elevation of {{convert|2300|m|ft|abbr=on}}.<ref name="mp"/>
The national park is of historical importance, where during the [[Battle of Sarikamish]] at the beginning of [[World War I]] about 60,000 Turkish soldiers died freezing under harsh winter conditions on the Allahuekber Mountains.<ref name="mp"/><ref name="hdn1"/>
